               <head xml:lang="en">Image Capture 4: Capturing UVL images</head>
               <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en">Ultraviolet-induced luminescence (UVL) images record the
      emission of light (luminescence) in the visible region (400-700 nm) from a subject when this
      is illuminated with UV radiation. This image is used to investigate the distribution of
      luminescent materials, such as organic binders and colorants.</desc>
